refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
intgetservbyname stringservice stringprotocol
getservbyname returns the Internet port which corresponds to service for the specified protocol as per /etc/services.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the port number, or &false; if service or
 protocol is not found.

  &reftitle.examples;



    getservbyname example


<?php
$services = array('http', 'ftp', 'ssh', 'telnet', 'imap',
'smtp', 'nicname', 'gopher', 'finger', 'pop3', 'www');

foreach ($services as $service) {
    $port = getservbyname($service, 'tcp');
    echo $service . ": " . $port . "<br />\n";
}
?>

&reftitle.seealso;



  getservbyport

   &url.network.port-numbers;
   for a complete list of port numbers.
